# 🔐 CYSEC - Day 4: Dictionary Attack vs Brute Force

## 📌 Overview

On Day 4, I explored the difference between **Brute Force Attacks** and **Dictionary Attacks**, focusing on efficiency and real-world usage.

---

## ⚙️ Brute Force vs Dictionary Attack

| Feature          | Brute Force Attack     | Dictionary Attack |
| ---------------- | ---------------------- | ----------------- |
| Method           | Tries all combinations | Uses a wordlist   |
| Speed            | Slow                   | Faster            |
| Efficiency       | Low                    | High              |
| Real-world usage | Less common            | More common       |

---

## 💻 What I Built

A Python-based simulation that:

* Reads passwords from a wordlist (`passwords.txt`)
* Attempts login using each password
* Stops when the correct password is found

---

## 🧠 Key Concepts Learned

* Attack optimization techniques
* Importance of wordlists in cybersecurity
* Real-world attack strategies
* Efficiency vs completeness in attacks

---

## 🛡️ Security Insights

* Avoid using common passwords
* Use long and complex passwords
* Enable Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)
* Regularly update passwords

